President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Mark Green as a member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Green is currently the President of the International Republican Institute and has previously served as President and CEO of the Initiative for Global Development. He has also been a member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation and the Senior Director of the U.S. Global Leadership Coalition. Additionally, Green served as the U.S. Ambassador to the United Republic of Tanzania and was a member of the U.S. House of Representatives for four terms. He holds a B.A. from the University of Wisconsin - Eau Claire and a J.D. from the University of Wisconsin School of Law.